Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
compare_power_intent(25.10)                        compare_power_intent(25.10)

Name
       compare_power_intent  - Compares the golden IEEE1801 and the hierarchi-
       cal IEEE1801 files generated by the Innovus hierarchical partition flow
       in terms of the low power database, and reports the mismatched category

Syntax
       compare_power_intent

       [-help]

       [-domain_attr]

       [-domain_boundary_port_constr]

       [-domain_map_file <file_name>]

       [-file_prefix <prefix>]

       -golden1801 <file_name>

        -hier1801 <file_name>

       [-pin_effective_domain]

       [-power_domains <list_of_domains>]

       [-verbose]

       Compares the golden IEEE1801 and the hierarchical IEEE1801 files gener-
       ated by the Innovus hierarchical partition flow in  terms  of  the  low
       power  database,  and  reports  the mismatched category. If there is no
       mismatch, the two IEEE1801 files are considered to be equivalent in the
       Innovus low power flow.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each compare_power_intent parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man compare_power_intent

       -domain_attr
              Compares low power attributes and properties of all the  attrib-
              utes,  which  include instance count, low power cell count, pri-
              mary supply, available supply, boundary,  port  low  power  con-
              straint, and effective domain counter for the leaf instance pin,
              and port.

       -domain_boundary_port_constr
              Compares  the  domain  boundary port IEEE1801 constraint against
              the golden IEEE1801.

       -domain_map_file <file_name>
              Specifies the domain map file saved during partition. The domain
              map file maps the golden IEEE1801  domain/supply  set/low  power
              signal  with  the  hierarchical  IEEE1801  domain/supply set/low
              power signal.

       -file_prefix <prefix>
              Specifies the file prefix for the report files.

       -golden1801 <file_name>
              Specifies the golden IEEE1801.

       -hier1801 <file_name>
              Specifies the hierarchical IEEE1801 to be compared.

       -pin_effective_domain
              Compares only the domain for leaf instance pin and port.

       -power_domains <list_of_domains>
              Specifies the list of specific power domains to be compared.

       -verbose
              Displays the detailed information related to each category.

Related Information
